<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Authors. (Year of publication). Title of article. <em>Name of Publication, volume</em>(issue), 
	page numbers. doi:Digital Object Identifier (if assigned)
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A., Brown, B., &amp; Chan, C.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2056</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Thinking critically in a whole new world</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Name of Publication">Language Learning in Higher Education</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume">24</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue">1</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">67&#45;87</span>. 
